
##
# Contains root .gitignore declarations for the current project instance
# using Common Web Tools.
#

# Public web dir (the application).
# There are 2 implementation approaches for using common web tools in a project :
#   1 • Keep application code in a separate Git repo
#   2 • Use a single, "monolothic" repo for everything
# → When using option 1, you may want to comment out the following line.
# You may also use a different folder name, such as 'public', 'build', etc.
/web

# Local environment variables.
/env/current/*
!/env/current/README.md

# Private files, outside of public (web) dir.
/private/*
!/private/README.md
!/private/.htaccess

# Custom scripts.
/scripts/custom
!/scripts/custom/README.md

# DB dumps.
/dumps/*
!/dumps/.keepme

# Misc.
docker-runtime
.idea
*.sql
